               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-378" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-378" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-378" type="surname" value="ELLIOTT"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-378" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>RICHARD ELLIOTT</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep a beer-shop, at Paddington—the prisoner was my servant. On 6th July I left a half-crown in my till—I went up stairs, heard the till rattle, came down, and a man had caught the prisoner—the half-crown was gone.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-379" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-379" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-379" type="surname" value="LITTLEBURY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-379" type="given" value="GEORGE"></interp>GEORGE LITTLEBURY</persName>
                  </hi>. I went into the beer-shop, and saw the prisoner leaning over the counter, with his hand in the till—he turned, and said to me, "What is for you, sir?"—I gave information.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner's Defence.</hi> I was cleaning the bar and moving the glasses; I never took the money out of the till.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18480821-name-380" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-380" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-380" type="surname" value="BRANDON"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18480821-name-380" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES BRANDON</persName>
                  </hi>. I was in the tap-room, and heard Mr. Elliott say he had lost half-a-crown—I came out—he had got hold of the prisoner—he gave him to, me while lie drew a pint of beet—I found this half-crown in a spittoon near where the prisoner had been.</p>
